  "Systematic error; they should take fewer measurements to reduce the effect": "",
  "A consistent offset of +2 degrees is a systematic error. It cannot be fixed by averaging. The solution is to recalibrate the thermometer or subtract 2 degrees from every reading.": "",
  "A student measures velocity as 4.0 +/- 0.2 m/s and time as 3.0 +/- 0.1 s. They calculate distance = velocity x time. What is the percentage uncertainty in the distance?": "",
